      About the Trial
    %div{ style: "max-width: 600px;font-size: 1.25rem;font-weight: 300;" }
      %p
        Healthy Sleep for Children with Down Syndrome (HELP-DS) is a research study to collect information about children with Down Syndrome (DS) who are undergoing adenotonsillectomy (AT) to address the childâ€™s sleep-disordered breathing (SDB). Removal of the tonsils and adenoids is a common treatment for SDB, but this has not been well studied, particularly in children with DS. Despite being at an increased risk of SDB and its associated risks, there is a lack of information on best clinical practices for children with DS in this situation.

      %p
        This lack of information is due to DS children being regularly left out of most studies looking at these conditions. HELP-DS wants to gather information on these children to decide how to effectively design future studies looking at children with DS and SDB. The information collected will look at how children are recruited, how they complete standardized assessments, their responsiveness to treatment, and various other aspects of participation in a research study.
